text: Komsai Pageant undergoes gender-inclusive 'rebranding' Computer Science students from the University of the Philippines Cebu (UPC) are set to launch an inclusive pageant by the end of the month. For the past… More years, UP Computer Science Guild (UPCSG) has culminated their annual Komsai Week with Bb. Komsai, a pageant featuring cisgender men in drag. However, students expressed that although the concept helped male students embrace their femininity, it also gave signs of “mockery.”  In response, the college organization seeks to rebrand the event by embracing “diversity, equity, and inclusion in technology.”  Main Director and Project Lead Gabriel Howard Awatin shared that they want to open the… More
